 Java Introduction

ðŸ”¹ What is Java?

Java is a high-level, object-oriented, platform-independent programming language developed in 1995 by James Gosling at Sun Microsystems (now owned by Oracle).


---

ðŸ”¹ Features of Java

1. Simple â†’ Easy to learn, syntax similar to C/C++.


2. Object-Oriented â†’ Everything is based on objects (classes, objects, inheritance).


3. Platform Independent â†’ "Write Once, Run Anywhere" (WORA) concept.


4. Secure â†’ Strong memory management and security features.


5. Robust â†’ Automatic garbage collection and exception handling.


6. Multithreaded â†’ Can perform multiple tasks simultaneously.


7. High Performance â†’ Uses JIT (Just-In-Time) compiler for faster execution.




---

ðŸ”¹ How Java Works?

Java code runs in three steps:

1. Write Code â†’ Save program in a .java file


2. Compile â†’ Java Compiler converts it into .class file (Bytecode)


3. Run â†’ JVM (Java Virtual Machine) executes the Bytecode




